reviews.review: A very satisfying conclusion to one of the great epics

This isn't close to being the best Star Wars movie out there but it's better than anything Disney has put out so far (except The Mandalorian). JJ did what he could after the terrible movie that shall not be named, and he did it well. Overall it was enjoyable.

It was good. Not great. Definitely much more improved from Last Jedi but that was a different director. The aesthetic, action, and cinematography was nicely done. Some cheap plot tricks, but overall they wrapped up the series nicely.

This movie was very predictable. They added in too many characters. Special effects were ok, but the story line needed a lot of help. Was very disappointed. Star wars should have ended at return of the Jedi, they way it was intended to. With bringing people and places back, it leaves it open for more movies.
If looking to see this movie, wait for it to come out on DVD. Don't waist your money.

Out of the 9 I rank it 4. Action from beginning to end. Plot was kinda rushed and not sure what ones ambitions were. (Without giving a spoiler) The other three I like better was IV, V, VI. Best of the last three for sure.

I have read alot of articles and headlines being negative about this movie so I was worried about watching it. After watching the movie I loved it and alot of my friends and coworkers as well can't stop talking about how amazing it was and how they went all out with the graphics and war scenes. This is now my favorite Star wars movie. Go watch it and don't look at the articles bashing it. It's one person's review over the people who have watched it.
Lots of action and true to the heart of all of the Star Wars movies. Fun.
Not my favorite movie but way better than TLJ a movie I really hate it

SOS -- Saved Our Skywalker. I have been a fan since the beginning. I really enjoyed it as I saw the Skywalker that I grew up and loved.  I loved the throw-backs and nostalgia, and I enjoyed the ending.  Was it perfect? No.  Was it good? Yes.

While not the best entry in the Star Wars franchise, or even the best movie overall, it's not a bad finale to the 40 year old saga. Could have been better, could have been a lot worse (looking at you, Bayformers). There is no way that ANY movie would have made every fan happy.
